-- round-16: 30 Cell programs that are impossible in beads formulas
-- Each requires recursion, validation gates, dynamic spawning, or self-modification.
-- Every execution MUST include cell-v0.1-spec.md as context.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- CATEGORY: SELF-EVOLVING PROGRAMS
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- 1. RESEARCH PLAN EVOLVER
-- Takes a problem statement, generates hypotheses, designs experiments
-- to test each hypothesis, evaluates which experiments are feasible,
-- SPAWNS new cells for feasible experiments, collects results,
-- rewrites hypotheses based on results. Loops until convergence.
-- Formula can't: dynamic spawning based on LLM judgment + recursive refinement.

-- 2. SELF-IMPROVING PROMPT
-- Takes a prompt + evaluation criteria. Runs the prompt, scores output,
-- identifies weaknesses, rewrites the prompt to fix weaknesses, re-runs,
-- re-scores. Loop until score exceeds threshold or max iterations.
-- Formula can't: output-dependent branching + quality gate loops.

-- 3. PROGRESSIVE CRYSTALLIZATION
-- Takes a soft task ("write a function that..."), generates code,
-- extracts the PATTERN, converts pattern to a ⊢= template, tests
-- template against new inputs, iterates until the template handles
-- all cases deterministically. The cell literally evolves from ⊢ to ⊢=.
-- Formula can't: substrate transfer as a runtime operation.

-- 4. SELF-BUILDING TEST SUITE
-- Takes a function signature + behavior description. Generates test
-- case 1, runs it, finds edge cases from the result, generates
-- targeted test cases for edges, runs those, finds deeper edges.
-- Spawns a new test cell for each discovered edge case.
-- Formula can't: recursive discovery + dynamic spawning.

-- 5. META-CELL DESIGNER
-- Takes a problem domain description. Designs a Cell program for it.
-- Evaluates the design via simulated eval-one. Finds awkward parts.
-- Redesigns. Outputs a ready-to-run .cell file.
-- Formula can't: programs that write programs with validation.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- CATEGORY: ADVERSARIAL / DIALECTIC
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- 6. SPEC HARDENER
-- Takes any specification text. An attacker cell finds ambiguities.
-- A defender cell rewrites to close them. A judge cell rules whether
-- the fix works. Loop until attacker can't find any more ambiguities.
-- Formula can't: multi-role adversarial loop with judgment gates.

-- 7. RECURSIVE DEBATE
-- Two cells argue opposing positions on a question. A judge scores
-- each round. Weak arguments get replaced, strong ones get refined.
-- Continues until no argument can be improved (fixpoint).
-- Formula can't: multi-agent with per-round quality evolution.

-- 8. RED-TEAM THEN HARDEN
-- Takes a piece of code. Red-team cell finds a vulnerability.
-- Fix cell patches it. Red-team attacks the patch. Loop until
-- red-team fails to find anything. Each round spawns oracle cells
-- that become permanent regression tests.
-- Formula can't: adversarial loop that ACCUMULATES artifacts.

-- 9. NEGOTIATION TO CONSENSUS
-- N perspective cells each argue a position. A mediator identifies
-- common ground and remaining disagreements. Perspective cells
-- revise. Mediator re-evaluates. Loop until supermajority consensus.
-- Formula can't: N-way parallel + judgment-gated iteration.

-- 10. SOCRATIC TEACHER
-- Takes a concept + student knowledge level. Asks a question.
-- Evaluates the answer (simulated student). Identifies misconception.
-- Designs targeted question to expose the misconception. Repeats
-- until student demonstrates understanding. Spawns remedial cells
-- for each misconception discovered.
-- Formula can't: adaptive branching based on diagnostic evaluation.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- CATEGORY: RECURSIVE DECOMPOSITION
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- 11. FRACTAL TASK PLANNER
-- Takes a goal. Decomposes into 3-5 sub-goals. Each sub-goal
-- decomposes into 3-5 tasks. Each task into steps. Each step into
-- atomic actions. Oracle at each level: "is this decomposition
-- complete and non-overlapping?" ⊥ if not → retry decomposition.
-- Formula can't: recursive depth with quality gates at each level.

-- 12. RECURSIVE REQUIREMENT EXTRACTOR
-- Takes a vague request ("build me an app"). Extracts explicit
-- requirements. Identifies implicit requirements. For each implicit
-- requirement, asks "what sub-requirements does this imply?"
-- Recurses until all requirements are concrete and testable.
-- Formula can't: recursive depth controlled by semantic judgment.

-- 13. PROGRESSIVE SUMMARIZATION
-- Takes a long document. Pass 1: summarize to 50%. Oracle: key info
-- preserved? Pass 2: summarize to 25%. Oracle: still accurate?
-- Continue halving until oracle says information loss is unacceptable.
-- The ⊥ from the oracle STOPS the loop — bottom as a feature.
-- Formula can't: oracle-terminated recursion (⊥ as stop signal).

-- 14. DEPENDENCY GRAPH BUILDER
-- Takes a codebase description. Identifies modules. For each module,
-- identifies dependencies. For each dependency, checks if it's
-- internal or external. For internal deps, recurses into that module.
-- Builds a complete DAG. Oracle validates: is the DAG acyclic?
-- Formula can't: recursive graph construction with structural validation.

-- 15. RECURSIVE EXPLANATION
-- Explains a concept. Identifies the 3 hardest sub-concepts.
-- Explains each sub-concept. Identifies THEIR hard parts. Recurses.
-- Stops when all leaf explanations pass a "would a 10-year-old
-- understand this?" oracle.
-- Formula can't: recursive depth controlled by comprehension oracle.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- CATEGORY: GENERATIVE / CREATIVE
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- 16. EVOLUTION SIMULATOR
-- Population of 6 solution candidates. Each generation: mutate each,
-- evaluate fitness via oracle, select top 3, crossover to produce 3
-- new candidates. Loop until fitness threshold or generation limit.
-- Formula can't: population-based parallel evolution with selection.

-- 17. COLLABORATIVE WORLD-BUILDER
-- Start with a seed: "a city where..." One cell adds geography.
-- One adds history. One adds culture. Each reads the others' outputs.
-- Consistency oracle checks for contradictions. If contradiction found,
-- the contradicting cell rewrites. Loop until consistent.
-- Formula can't: parallel creative generation with consistency oracle.

-- 18. RECURSIVE STORY BUILDER
-- Generates a story outline (3 acts). Each act spawns cells for
-- scenes. Each scene spawns cells for beats. Oracle checks narrative
-- consistency across spawned levels. Bottom-up assembly: beats →
-- scenes → acts → story.
-- Formula can't: hierarchical spawning with cross-level validation.

-- 19. CODE GENERATOR WITH PROOF
-- Takes a function spec. Generates code. Generates property-based
-- tests. Runs tests (simulated). If failure: analyzes failure,
-- rewrites code, re-tests. If pass: generates a proof sketch
-- explaining why the code is correct. Oracle validates proof.
-- Formula can't: generate-test-fix loop + proof generation.

-- 20. LANGUAGE DESIGNER
-- Takes a domain ("financial contracts"). Designs a DSL for it.
-- Writes 3 example programs in the DSL. Tries to eval-one each.
-- Identifies where the DSL is awkward. Redesigns. Re-writes examples.
-- Loop until all examples execute cleanly.
-- Formula can't: meta-language design with eval-one feedback loop.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- CATEGORY: VALIDATION-HEAVY
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- 21. SELF-CORRECTING TRANSLATOR
-- Translates text to target language. Back-translates to source.
-- Diff oracle compares source vs back-translation. If drift detected:
-- identifies drifted segments, retranslates just those, re-checks.
-- Loop until back-translation matches within oracle tolerance.
-- Formula can't: bidirectional validation loop with segment-level retry.

-- 22. FACT-CHECKED ARTICLE
-- Generates an article on a topic. For each factual claim, spawns
-- a fact-check oracle cell. Failed claims get rewritten or removed.
-- Re-generates article without bad claims. Re-checks new claims.
-- Loop until all claims pass.
-- Formula can't: dynamic oracle spawning per claim + rewrite loop.

-- 23. MULTI-ORACLE GANTLET
-- Takes LLM output through 5 different oracle types: structural
-- (format check), semantic (meaning check), factual (truth check),
-- stylistic (tone check), logical (consistency check). If ANY fails,
-- the output gets rewritten targeting the failed oracle, then
-- re-runs ALL oracles. Loop until all 5 pass simultaneously.
-- Formula can't: multi-dimensional validation with targeted retry.

-- 24. PROOF-CARRYING CODE
-- Takes a function + its spec. Generates code + a formal argument
-- for correctness. Validates argument structure (is it actually a
-- proof?). If invalid: identifies the gap, regenerates just that
-- part of the argument, re-validates. Code + proof ship together.
-- Formula can't: coupled generation + validation with gap-targeted retry.

-- 25. ORACLE CHAIN BUILDER
-- Takes a soft oracle ("output is good"). Asks: what does "good" mean?
-- Decomposes into 3 specific sub-oracles. For each sub-oracle,
-- asks if IT is still too vague. Recurses until all leaf oracles are
-- deterministically checkable (⊢=). Outputs an oracle hierarchy.
-- Formula can't: recursive oracle refinement from vague to precise.

-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-- CATEGORY: META / SELF-REFERENTIAL
-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

-- 26. CELL-ZERO EXERCISER
-- Takes cell-zero.cell and a simple target program. Traces cell-zero
-- executing the target step by step. At each step, validates that
-- cell-zero's behavior matches the spec. Identifies any divergence
-- between cell-zero-as-written and cell-zero-as-spec.
-- Formula can't: metacircular execution trace with spec validation.

-- 27. SELF-OPTIMIZING CELL
-- Takes a working Cell program. Analyzes it for redundant cells,
-- tautological oracles, unnecessary dependencies. Removes them.
-- Re-executes the optimized version. Compares output. If different:
-- the optimization was wrong — revert and try a different optimization.
-- Formula can't: optimization loop with correctness-preserving constraint.

-- 28. PROGRAM ALGEBRA PROVER
-- Takes two Cell programs. Claims they're equivalent. Traces both
-- via eval-one. Compares outputs at each step. If divergence found:
-- identifies the cause, determines if it's a real semantic difference
-- or just an ordering difference (confluence). Outputs: equivalent
-- or not, with proof trace.
-- Formula can't: parallel execution + semantic comparison + proof.

-- 29. BOOTSTRAPPER
-- Starts with ZERO cells. A meta-cell reads a problem description.
-- Decides what cells are needed. Spawns them (via ⊢⊢). Spawned cells
-- execute. Meta-cell reads results. Decides if more cells are needed.
-- Spawns more. Loop until the problem is solved. The program
-- literally builds itself from nothing.
-- Formula can't: fully dynamic program construction.

-- 30. CELL SPEC EVOLVER
-- Takes the current Cell v0.1 spec. Writes a program that's awkward
-- in the current spec. Identifies WHY it's awkward. Proposes a spec
-- change. Rewrites the program with the proposed change. Evaluates:
-- is it better? If yes, the spec change is good. Accumulates changes.
-- Loop until no more awkwardness found. Outputs: proposed v0.2 spec.
-- Formula can't: meta-language evolution driven by usage feedback.
